	(text "i²c MODULE\n\nThis module is the most suitable\nfor multiple devices by using i²c\nprotocol. i²c gives the developer\nfreedom by its addressing system."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 280.162 75.692 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify right top)
		)
		(uuid "1aac926d-7108-4ea0-952c-5c34b3402c56")
	)
	(text "GND"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 226.568 27.686 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify right top)
		)
		(uuid "22fb2bbe-63de-4273-8c16-ae867607033c")
	)
	(text "ANALOG MODULE\n\nBy using a simple voltage divider,\nit gives back an exact representation\nof where all the LINEAR potmeters\nposition are."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 280.416 150.876 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify right top)
		)
		(uuid "3813d483-930c-43b2-9d2e-cc170b96bac9")
	)
	(text "CARRIER BOARD for arduino pro micro DEVBOARD\nMCU: ATMEL ATMEGA32u4\nCLK: 16MHz\n\nThis carrier is required to specialize and \npriotize features and functionalities.\nThis simple method would give the project \nflexibility for creating a customizeable and modular platform.\nBy using modular modules and carriers it simplifying the \nupgrade of any component inside.\nThis means that any modules or carrier can be used and reused in\nother projects, and by using the schematic, it could be easy to\nintegrate it."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 190.754 77.978 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.778 1.778)
			)
			(justify right top)
		)
		(uuid "392dbb20-0c0f-4d9f-b664-ecc60fa1380d")
	)
